The article is about President Trump awarding the Congressional Medal of Honor to Staff Sergeant David Bellavia, the first living recipient to earn the medal for his bravery in the Iraq War. The ceremony took place in the East Room, and the President recognized other military leaders and members of Congress who were present. The article highlights the heroic actions of Staff Sergeant Bellavia during the Battle of Fallujah, where he single-handedly defeated multiple insurgents, rescued his squad, and cleared an entire enemy-filled house. The President praised Staff Sergeant Bellavia's courage and selflessness, and emphasized the importance of American valor in protecting the nation. The article concludes with the President presenting the Medal of Honor to Staff Sergeant Bellavia.